Goal

Exploration of power simulation results from the test_data dataset.

Power across effect sizes

The statistical power to detect different effect sizes was computed by simulating UMI count data and injecting the specified effect sizes (% decrease in expression). Here, the statistical power and the number of E-G pairs is at 80% power plotted for effect sizes.

Power vs. gene expression and number of perturbed cells

Power is plotted as a function of gene expression levels and number of perturbed cells per perturbation. For this, genes are binned into decentiles based on their average expression (UMI or TPM/cell). For each bin, the average UMI or TPM/cell per gene is then calculated and used as the expression level for genes in this bin. Similarly, the perturbations are grouped into quartiles based on the number of cells per perturbation. The average statistical power per expression bin is then plotted as a function of detected UMIs for each cells per perturbation quartile.
